      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "AFFAMATO (8) overcame a wide draw for a resuming win at this circuit and distance then missed by just a neck from this barrier over further last start at Ballarat. Better suited at this trip having won two of three attempts and he shouldn't spend a penny from this draw. FLIP A COIN (12) in in strong form having won his last two outings at Wagga. Came from a similar draw to this when runner-up three back at Shepparton and is proven at this circuit and distance. Leading hope. DUSTY PHILTRA (13) is in good form winning twice in three starts so far this campaign and came from this row for second in the other outing. Must respect. Tricky draw for LONGTAN VIPER (10) but he was rewarded for his recent consistency with a last-start win at Shepparton.",
